18.13	Danny_Jordaan	Danny Jordaan	Daniel Alexander "Danny" Jordaan (born September 3, 1951) is a South African sports administrator as well as a former lecturer, politician and anti-apartheid activist. He led South Africa's successful 2010 FIFA World Cup bid, the first successful one for Africa. He also led their unsuccessful bid four years earlier for the 2006 FIFA World Cup. He was also the Chief Executive Officer of the 2010 FIFA World Cup South Africa.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/93/Daniel_Jordaan%2C_2009_World_Economic_Forum_on_Africa-2.jpg/220px-Daniel_Jordaan%2C_2009_World_Economic_Forum_on_Africa-2.jpg
